<hr class="section-divider">

<!-- SECTION 6 -->
<h1 id="registration">6. User Registration &amp; Login</h1>

<h2>6.1 Creating a New Account</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Go to <strong>http://localhost:5173</strong></li>
  <li>Click <strong>Sign Up</strong> in the top-right corner of the navigation bar</li>
  <li>Fill in the registration form:
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Full Name</strong> — your display name</li>
      <li><strong>Email</strong> — must be a real email format (e.g., yourname@gmail.com). Disposable email domains are blocked.</li>
      <li><strong>Password</strong> — minimum 8 characters</li>
      <li><strong>Role</strong> — select <strong>Buyer</strong> or <strong>Seller</strong></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Click <strong>Create Account</strong></li>
</ol>

<div class="note">
  <strong>Role difference:</strong> Buyers can browse, save favorites, and book viewings. Sellers can do everything buyers can, plus they can add and manage property listings.
</div>

<h2>6.2 Logging In</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Click <strong>Sign In</strong> in the navigation bar</li>
  <li>Enter your email and password</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Sign In</strong></li>
</ol>

<p>Once logged in, the navigation bar will show your role-specific options.</p>

<h2>6.3 Forgot Password</h2>

<ol>
  <li>On the Sign In page, click <strong>Forgot Password?</strong></li>
  <li>Enter your registered email address</li>
  <li>Check your email for a reset link (requires email/SMTP to be configured in <code>backend/.env.local</code>)</li>
  <li>Click the link in the email and set a new password</li>
</ol>

<hr class="section-divider">

<!-- SECTION 7 -->
<h1 id="browsing">7. Browsing Properties</h1>

<h2>7.1 Properties Page</h2>

<p>Click <strong>Properties</strong> in the navigation bar to open the full property listing. You will see:</p>

<ul>
  <li>A <strong>filter sidebar</strong> on the left</li>
  <li>A <strong>grid of property cards</strong> on the right</li>
  <li>Quick-filter <strong>type chips</strong> (Apartment, House, Villa, Office) above the grid</li>
</ul>

<h2>7.2 Using the Filter Sidebar</h2>

<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Filter</th>
    <th>How to Use</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>Location</strong></td>
    <td>Type a city or neighborhood name (e.g., "Koramangala", "Mumbai"). The list filters in real time.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>Availability</strong></td>
    <td>Click <strong>Buy</strong> or <strong>Rent</strong> to show only listings for sale or rent.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>Price Range</strong></td>
    <td>Drag the slider handles to set a minimum and maximum price. Values display in Lakhs (L) and Crores (Cr).</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>Property Type</strong></td>
    <td>Tick one or more checkboxes: Apartment, House, Villa, Office.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>Bedrooms / Bathrooms</strong></td>
    <td>Click a number to filter by minimum bedrooms or bathrooms.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>Amenities</strong></td>
    <td>Tick amenities like Parking, Swimming Pool, Gym, etc. Only properties with ALL selected amenities will show.</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p>A blue badge on the sidebar header shows how many filters are currently active. Click <strong>Reset all</strong> to clear all filters at once.</p>

<h2>7.3 Sorting Properties</h2>

<p>Use the <strong>Sort</strong> dropdown at the top-right of the grid to change the order:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Featured</strong> — default order</li>
  <li><strong>Price: Low to High</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Price: High to Low</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Newest First</strong> — most recently added listings first</li>
  <li><strong>Most Beds</strong></li>
</ul>

<h2>7.4 Grid vs List View</h2>

<p>Click the grid or list icons at the top-right to switch between views.</p>

<h2>7.5 Property Badges</h2>

<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Badge</th>
    <th>Meaning</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>FOR SALE</td>
    <td>Property is available for purchase</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>FOR RENT</td>
    <td>Property is available for rent</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>SOLD</td>
    <td>Property is no longer available</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>NEW</td>
    <td>Property was listed within the last 45 days</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<hr class="section-divider">

<!-- SECTION 8 -->
<h1 id="property-details">8. Property Details Page</h1>

<p>Click any property card to open the full detail page. This page includes:</p>

<h2>8.1 Property Information</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Hero image gallery</li>
  <li>Price, address, number of beds, baths, and square footage</li>
  <li>Full property description with estimated reading time</li>
  <li>Amenities list</li>
  <li>Location map</li>
</ul>

<h2>8.2 EMI Calculator (Sidebar)</h2>

<p>The right sidebar includes an interactive EMI calculator:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Adjust the <strong>Down Payment</strong> slider (10% to 50%)</li>
  <li>Adjust the <strong>Interest Rate</strong> slider (6% to 15%)</li>
  <li>Adjust the <strong>Loan Tenure</strong> slider (5 to 30 years)</li>
  <li>The calculator instantly shows: Loan Amount, Monthly EMI, Total Interest, and Total Payment</li>
</ol>

<div class="note">
  <strong>Note:</strong> These are indicative figures only. Consult your bank for actual loan terms.
</div>

<h2>8.3 Share &amp; Enquire Buttons</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Share Property</strong> — copies the property page URL to your clipboard. A "Link Copied!" confirmation appears for 2 seconds.</li>
  <li><strong>WhatsApp Enquiry</strong> — opens WhatsApp with a pre-filled message about the property.</li>
</ul>

<h2>8.4 Similar Properties</h2>

<p>Scroll to the bottom of the property detail page to see up to 3 similar properties from the same city. Click any to open that listing.</p>

<h2>8.5 Scroll Progress Bar</h2>

<p>A thin blue progress bar at the very top of the page tracks how far down the page you have scrolled.</p>

<hr class="section-divider">

<!-- SECTION 9 -->
<h1 id="favorites">9. Saving Favorites</h1>

<p>You must be logged in to save favorites.</p>

<ol>
  <li>On any property card, click the <strong>heart icon</strong> in the top-right corner of the card image</li>
  <li>The heart turns blue when the property is saved</li>
  <li>To view all your saved properties, click <strong>Saved</strong> in the navigation bar</li>
  <li>To remove a property from favorites, click the heart icon again</li>
</ol>

<div class="note">
  If you click the heart icon while not logged in, you will be redirected to the Sign In page.
</div>

<hr class="section-divider">

<!-- SECTION 10 -->
<h1 id="appointments">10. Scheduling a Property Viewing</h1>

<p>You can book a viewing both as a guest (without logging in) or while logged in.</p>

<h2>10.1 Booking a Viewing</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open any property detail page</li>
  <li>On the right sidebar, find the <strong>Schedule a Viewing</strong> form</li>
  <li>Fill in your <strong>Full Name</strong>, <strong>Email Address</strong>, and <strong>Phone Number</strong></li>
  <li>Select a <strong>Preferred Date</strong></li>
  <li>Select a <strong>Time Slot</strong> from the dropdown (9 AM to 5 PM)</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Schedule Visit</strong></li>
</ol>

<p>On success, you will see a green confirmation message. The seller will be notified.</p>

<h2>10.2 Viewing Your Appointments</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Log in to your account</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Appointments</strong> in the navigation bar</li>
  <li>All your scheduled, confirmed, and completed viewings are listed here</li>
  <li>You can cancel a pending appointment from this page</li>
</ol>

<hr class="section-divider">

<!-- SECTION 11 -->
<h1 id="seller">11. Seller Features</h1>

<p>Seller features are only visible when you are logged in as a user with the <strong>Seller</strong> role.</p>

<h2>11.1 Adding a New Property</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Log in as a seller</li>
  <li>Click <strong>+ List Property</strong> in the navigation bar</li>
  <li>Fill in the property details:
    <table>
      <tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Title</td><td>Name of the property (e.g., "3BHK Luxury Apartment in Indiranagar")</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Description</td><td>Detailed property description</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Price</td><td>Price in Indian Rupees (e.g., 7500000 for ₹75 Lakhs)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Location</td><td>Full address (e.g., "Indiranagar, Bengaluru, Karnataka")</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Type</td><td>Apartment / House / Villa / Office</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Availability</td><td>Buy / Rent / Sold</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Beds &amp; Baths</td><td>Number of bedrooms and bathrooms</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Area (sqft)</td><td>Total built-up area in square feet</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Phone</td><td>Contact phone number for enquiries</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Amenities</td><td>Tick all available amenities</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Images</td><td>Upload up to 4 property photos (JPG or PNG, max 10 MB each)</td></tr>
    </table>
  </li>
  <li>Click <strong>Add Property</strong> to publish the listing</li>
</ol>

<div class="note">
  Images are uploaded to ImageKit CDN automatically. If ImageKit keys are not configured, image uploads will fail but the property can still be saved without images.
</div>

<h2>11.2 Managing Your Listings</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Click <strong>My Listings</strong> in the navigation bar</li>
  <li>All properties you have listed are shown here</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Edit</strong> on any listing to update its details, price, or images</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Delete</strong> to permanently remove a listing</li>
</ol>

<h2>11.3 Viewing Incoming Requests</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Click <strong>Requests</strong> in the navigation bar (visible to sellers only)</li>
  <li>This page shows all appointment requests buyers have submitted for your properties</li>
  <li>For each request you can:
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Confirm</strong> — accept the viewing request</li>
      <li><strong>Decline</strong> — reject the request</li>
      <li><strong>Mark as Completed</strong> — mark after the visit has taken place</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<hr class="section-divider">

<!-- SECTION 12 -->
<h1 id="admin">12. Admin Dashboard</h1>

<h2>12.1 Accessing the Admin Panel</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open <strong>http://localhost:5174</strong> in your browser</li>
  <li>Log in with the admin credentials:</li>
</ol>

<div class="credential-box">
  Email:    admin@estatemanagement.com<br>
  Password: Admin@123456
</div>

<div class="warning">
  <strong>Important:</strong> The admin panel is completely separate from the main website. You cannot log in to the admin panel from http://localhost:5173. You must go directly to http://localhost:5174.
</div>

<h2>12.2 Dashboard Overview</h2>

<p>After logging in, you land on the <strong>Dashboard</strong>. It shows:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Total properties, total users, total appointments (counts)</li>
  <li>Recent activity log</li>
  <li>Charts showing listings over time and appointment status breakdown</li>
</ul>

<h2>12.3 Managing Properties</h2>

<h4>View All Properties</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Click <strong>Properties</strong> in the admin sidebar</li>
  <li>A table lists every property with title, price, location, type, and status</li>
</ol>

<h4>Add a New Property</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Click <strong>Add Property</strong> in the sidebar</li>
  <li>Fill in all the property details (same fields as the seller Add Property form)</li>
  <li>Upload images using the drag-and-drop area</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Add Property</strong> to save</li>
</ol>

<h4>Edit a Property</h4>
<ol>
  <li>On the Properties list, click the <strong>Edit</strong> icon next to a property</li>
  <li>Modify any fields</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Update Property</strong> to save changes</li>
</ol>

<h4>Delete a Property</h4>
<ol>
  <li>On the Properties list, click the <strong>Delete</strong> icon</li>
  <li>Confirm the deletion</li>
</ol>

<h2>12.4 Managing Appointments</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Click <strong>Appointments</strong> in the admin sidebar</li>
  <li>All viewing requests from all users are shown in a table</li>
  <li>For each appointment you can:
    <ul>
      <li>Change the <strong>status</strong> (Pending, Confirmed, Completed, Cancelled)</li>
      <li>Add a <strong>meeting link</strong> (e.g., Google Meet or Zoom URL) for virtual viewings</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<h2>12.5 Managing Users</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Click <strong>Users</strong> in the admin sidebar</li>
  <li>All registered user accounts are listed with their name, email, role, and join date</li>
  <li>You can view individual user profiles and their activity</li>
</ol>

<h2>12.6 Activity Logs</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Click <strong>Activity Logs</strong> in the admin sidebar</li>
  <li>A chronological log of admin actions is shown (property added/edited/deleted, status changes, etc.)</li>
</ol>

<hr class="section-divider">

<!-- SECTION 13 -->
<h1 id="contact">13. Contact Form</h1>

<ol>
  <li>Click <strong>Contact</strong> in the navigation bar</li>
  <li>Fill in: First Name, Last Name, Email, Phone Number, and Message (max 500 characters)</li>
  <li>A live character counter under the message field shows how many characters you have used</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Send Message</strong></li>
  <li>All submissions are saved to the database. The admin can view them from the Admin Dashboard.</li>
</ol>

<p>The contact page also shows office hours, location (Bengaluru, Karnataka), and a WhatsApp chat option.</p>

<hr class="section-divider">

<!-- SECTION 14 -->
<h1 id="tips">14. Common Issues &amp; Tips</h1>

<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Issue</th>
    <th>Cause &amp; Fix</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>White screen / nothing loads at http://localhost:5173</td>
    <td>Frontend is still starting. Wait 10–15 seconds and refresh the page.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>"Failed to load properties" error on Properties page</td>
    <td>Backend is not running. Make sure <code>npm run dev</code> is running in the root folder and the backend shows "Server running on port 4000".</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Admin login shows "Invalid credentials"</td>
    <td>Admin account has not been created yet. Run <code>node scripts/createAdmin.js</code> from the backend folder.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Registration fails with "Invalid email domain"</td>
    <td>The backend blocks disposable email providers. Use a real email address like a Gmail account.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Properties page shows 0 properties</td>
    <td>The database is empty. Run <code>node scripts/seedAll.js --force</code> from the backend folder to load demo data.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Image uploads fail when adding a property</td>
    <td>ImageKit API keys are not configured. Add your keys to <code>backend/.env.local</code> under <code>IMAGEKIT_PUBLIC_KEY</code>, <code>IMAGEKIT_PRIVATE_KEY</code>, and <code>IMAGEKIT_URL_ENDPOINT</code>.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Forgot password email is not received</td>
    <td>SMTP is not configured. Add Brevo SMTP credentials to <code>backend/.env.local</code> (<code>SMTP_USER</code>, <code>SMTP_PASS</code>, <code>EMAIL</code>).</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>MongoDB connection error on startup</td>
    <td>MongoDB is not running locally. Start the MongoDB service, or change <code>MONGO_URI</code> in <code>backend/.env.local</code> to a MongoDB Atlas connection string.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Port 4000 / 5173 / 5174 already in use</td>
    <td>Another process is using the port. Close the conflicting process or change the port in the respective <code>.env.local</code> file.</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<h2>General Tips</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Always run <code>npm run dev</code> from the <strong>root folder</strong>, not from inside backend or frontend.</li>
  <li>The backend must be running before the frontend can load any data.</li>
  <li>Changes to <code>.env.local</code> files require a server restart to take effect — stop <code>npm run dev</code> with Ctrl+C and run it again.</li>
  <li>The <strong>Recently Viewed</strong> strip on the Properties page is powered by your browser's localStorage. It clears if you clear your browser data.</li>
  <li>The <strong>Dark Mode</strong> toggle is in the top-right of the navigation bar.</li>
</ul>

